newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 917 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 917 contracts.

text.p: Chicago Board of Trade's Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totaled 917 contracts, according to the CBOT.
There were 54 wheat contracts, 571 corn and 292 soybean futures contracts traded, along with 18 corn call options.
The overnight trend for corn was 1-1/2 to 1/2 cents per bushel higher, soybeans 2-3/4 to four cents higher, and wheat 1-1/4 cent lower to 1/2 cent higher.
